Anger is mounting in Port Alfred over the inability of police to curb rampant public drinking. Local DA chief whip Ray Schenk yesterday said people were starting to see the popular coastal resort town as a place where rules and laws don t apply . It is all very worrying, he said. According to Schenk public drinking had steadily increased over the past five years.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions